# Outlook

Outlook stores data (mails, calendar, contacts) locally in a `.pst` or `.ost` data file.
Such files can be found in `C:\Users\username\AppData\Local\Microsoft\Outlook\`.


## Extract Outlook data via readpst on Linux

The tool `readpst` (https://github.com/pst-format/libpst) can be used to convert an Outlook data file to mbox files
or to extract individual emails and other files.

Process an Outlook data file and recursively create single email files in an output directory:
    readpst user@example.com.ost -r -S -o output/

Other output formats are supported.
